|postscript=.}}</ref> Tony Watson reviewed ''Star Saga: One - Beyond the Boundary'' in ''[[The Space Gamer|Space Gamer/Fantasy Gamer]]'' No. 84.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Watson|first=Tony |date=December 1988|title=Space Gamer Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer|Space Gamer/Fantasy Gamer]]|publisher=[[3W (company)|World Wide Wargames]]|issue=84|pages=26–27}}</ref> Watson commented that "Through imaginative writing, an appreciation of SF, and an appropriate sense of humor (and Will McLean's illustrations help too), the designers have made the paragraph system work. ''Star Saga: One'' is simply a lot of fun
